24/07/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The first meeting between representatives of the Montenegrin government and the European Commission under the framework of the Enhanced Permanent Dialogue will take place in Pogdorica on Monday (24 July). 
According to the ministry for International Economic Relations and European Integration, discussions will focus on the institutional environment in Montenegro following the independence referendum, the functioning of democratic institutions, the adoption of a new Montenegrin constitution, and human and minority rights. 
(Pobjeda - 24/07/06)
